~ high_start
do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base", "none", 0.0)
An ancient man leans back in his hospital chair.
The squint in his eyes seems to have relaxed.
do SoundManager.play_music_track("mcbucket_cannathink_theme", 5.0)
What do you say to him?
=> high_hub

~ high_hub
- Hey, how are you?
	do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
	Old Man: I...am. Yes.
	- Excuse me?
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base_mouth_open")
		Old Man: I would never accuse you of anything, friend.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
		Old Man: I think you are just...[i]splendid[/i].
		Is there anything else you want to say to him?
		=> high_hub

- Nice eyes, Old Man.
	do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
	Old Man: Thanks! Got 'em from my sister's side of the family, I think.
	- Your...sister's side?
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open")
		Old Man: Hehehe...Yeah. She's got great knees too. That woman.
		Is there anything else you want to say to him?
		=> high_hub

- Tell me something about yourself.
	do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base_mouth_open")
	Old Man: Something about...me?
	do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
	Old Man: What d'ya wanna know?
	=> high_hub2

- Nevermind [Leave]
	=> high_leave

~ high_hub2
- What's your name?
	do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open")
	Old Man: Sure! Do you wanna know my [i]worldly[/i] name... or my [i]real[/i] name?

	- Your worldly name.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base_mouth_open")
		Old Man: That would be... Mr. Turtle.
		- Mr. Turtle?
			do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open_2")
			Old Man: Yes. I rarely come outta my shell. And I swim. I always swim.
			- Okay... what's your real name then?
				=> love_branch

	- Your real name.
		=> love_branch

- How'd you end up here?
	do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base")
	Old Man: Here?
	Old Man: Where are we anyway?
	- We're at a hospital?
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
		Old Man: A hospital? Hahaha. Well I don't know how I ended up here.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open")
		Old Man: But I can tell ya one thing for sure - they're wasting their time having me here!
		Old Man: There ain't a damn thing wrong with Ol' McBucket over here.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base_mouth_open")
		Old Man: Well, except for my severe case of...
		- Of what?
			do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base")
			Old Man: Eh? What?
			The Old Man seems to have lost his train of thought.
			Do you want to talk about something else?
			=> high_hub2

- I'd like to ask some other questions [Back]
	What do you wanna say to him?
	=> high_hub

- Nevermind [Leave]
	=> high_leave

~ love_branch
Old Man: That would be...
do show_cg("mcbucket_high_hand_up")
Old Man: Love.
- Love? What do you mean?
	do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open_2")
	Old Man: I mean the only real thing in this world [i]is[/i] love.
	do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open")
	Old Man: Say, kid... you ever loved anyone before?

	- Yes.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
		Old Man: Hah! Then you already know what I'm talking about!
		Old Man: Hold onto it, kid. It's rarer than a polite seagull.
		Old Man: And when you find it again... feed it something nice.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base")
		You see the Old Man drift away into his own thoughts.
		Is there anything else you'd like to say to the Old Man?
		=> high_hub2

	- Not really.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
		Old Man: Then I hope it finds you soon! It's the most wonderful thing.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open_2")
		Old Man: Once you're in love... you see it everywhere.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_hand_up")
		Old Man: In the grass. In the tiles. On the screen. Even in the chips.

		- The chips?
			do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open")
			Old Man: Yeah. You got any on ya? I'm gettin' kinda hungry for some reason.
			The Old Man makes none and all the sense in the world at the same time.

			- Have you ever been in love?
				do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_closed_mouth_open")
				Old Man: Who? Me?
				do show_cg("mcbucket_high_hand_up")
				Old Man: I am [i]always[/i] in love.
				do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base_mouth_open")
				Old Man: It's not possible for me to [i]not[/i] be in it.
				Old Man: I only forget sometimes.
				do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
				Old Man: Once, I was walking down the street, and this RoboCop comes up to me and says...
				Old Man: ...
				do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base_mouth_open")
				Old Man: Wait—what was I talking about?
				=> high_hub2
			- I'd like to ask something else [Back]
				=> high_hub2
			- Nevermind [Leave]
				=> high_leave

	- I can't recall. I have no memories.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_base_mouth_open")
		Old Man: Oh boy, no memories huh?
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_open_mouth_open")
		Old Man: Who took 'em from ya? Did you check the fridge?
		You are reminded that you are talking to a person high out of their mind.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_explaining_eyes_closed_mouth_open")
		Old Man: Don't worry kiddo. Maybe they are just out for a swim.
		do show_cg("mcbucket_high_happy")
		Old Man: Maybe one day they'll swim right back to ya.
		The Old Man's words penetrate you deeply.
		Do you [i]want[/i] the memories to swim back to you?
		You silently brush away that thought.
		Is there anything else you'd like to say to the Old Man?
		=> high_hub2

~ high_leave
"Goodbye Old Man" you say to the character in front of you.
do SoundManager.fade_out_music(3.0)
=> END

~ invigirol_start
do show_cg("mcbucket_invigirol_base", "none", 0.0)
~ invigirol_loop
do shake(-1, 20.0)
Old Man McBucket: REEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE~~~~~!!!
- What?
	=> invigirol_loop
- Leave [Leave]
	"GOODBYE OLD MAN!" You say to the creature in front of you.
	=> END

~ sleeping_start
do change_background("mcbucket_background", "none", 0.0)
The Old Man is fast asleep.
=> END
